# DiffusionSystem

## Purpose
Drives in-engine text-to-image generation (ADR 0008). Returns early until the engine config and
resource map exist. Lazily creates the diffusion backend + job + matting backend singletons (deferred),
then loads the resident checkpoint (+ optional ControlNet) and the resident matting model once from the
resource map's model paths. Each frame it reaps a finished Diffusion Job — emitting a
RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest carrying the result — and, while idle and the backend is loaded,
assembles one GenerateImageRequest into backend job parameters (resolving Generation Config defaults,
LoRA UUIDs to paths, and the OpenPose Control Hint by rasterizing the referenced skeleton) and launches a
single generation on a background worker thread so the frame loop never blocks. Only one job runs at a time.

The worker may composite the generated subject over a background image (resolved like an Input Image),
choosing the alpha source by precedence (ADR 0012): the figure's per-pixel **Alpha Matte** from the
Matting Backend (m_CompositeWithMatte) → the OpenPose skeleton's **silhouette mask**
(m_CompositeWithSkeletonMask, also the matte's fallback when the Matting Backend is unavailable) →
**chroma key**. The matte is computed on the worker (it needs the generated figure); the skeleton
silhouette is resolved on the main thread and captured as the fallback. The composite is a CPU blend, so
it cannot produce the flat grey that img2img + ControlNet does on the bundled checkpoint.

It also drains any RasterizeOpenPoseHintRequest each frame (ADR 0011): for each, it resolves the
referenced skeleton, rasterizes the canonical OpenPose hint at the requested size (falling back to the
Generation Config defaults), and emits a RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest so the pose can be shown as an
ordinary texture. This is synchronous CPU work independent of the job machinery; an unknown skeleton is
skipped with a warning. It owns this because RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest has a single adder.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| GenerateImageRequestOneFrameComponent | read | App-emitted request: prompt, overrides, LoRA refs, optional OpenPose ControlNet, target UUID |
| RasterizeOpenPoseHintRequestOneFrameComponent | read | App-emitted request: skeleton UUID + target texture UUID + size; rasterized to a shown texture (ADR 0011) |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read | Resident checkpoint/ControlNet/VAE paths, LoRA paths, OpenPose skeletons, matting model paths, input/background images |
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | Generation Config defaults for unset request fields |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| DiffusionBackendSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once (holds the platform backend); m_LoadAttempted guards the one-time checkpoint load |
| DiffusionJobSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Holds the single active/just-finished job (worker thread + atomic state + result) |
| MattingBackendSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once (holds the matting backend); m_LoadAttempted guards the one-time matting-model load (ADR 0012) |
| RegisterGeneratedTextureRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted when a job completes (and for a rasterized OpenPose hint); drained by ResourceManagerSystem |
